<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 4:29PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Talladega
and southwestern Clay Counties through 500 PM CDT...
At 428 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Winterboro, or 7 miles south of Talladega, moving southeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Waldo, Chandler Springs and Gunthertown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
